Four pupils of the Local Education Authority Primary School, Alwaza in Doma local government area of Nasarawa State have regained their freedom from kidnappers. Six children of the school were last two weeks abducted by armed gunmen who later released two of the victims. DAILY POST recalls that the pupils were kidnapped when the bandits ambushed them in the morning as they were entering their school. There has not been any official report from the police on the release of the remaining four pupils.